## 1. Purpose

BRAHM-AI is an India-first artificial intelligence ecosystem developed to combine:

* Indian knowledge and scripture intelligence;
* multilingual language understanding;
* voice and avatar interaction;
* computer vision and OCR;
* Panchang and Jyotish computation;
* automation and connected digital actions;
* agriculture, education, market, and business intelligence;
* local and sovereign AI research;
* developer APIs and specialized AI services.

The project may be publicly visible for transparency, technical documentation, collaboration, demonstration, and community awareness.

Public visibility does **not** make BRAHM-AI open source and does not grant permission to copy, modify, distribute, deploy, train from, imitate, or commercially exploit any protected material.

---

## 2. Definitions

For this License:

### 2.1 “BRAHM-AI”

“BRAHM-AI” means the complete BRAHM-AI ecosystem, including its websites, applications, APIs, models, agents, modules, services, documentation, interfaces, datasets, and associated technology.

### 2.2 “Licensor”

“Licensor” means the Ramcoin Foundation, Royal Web 3 Blockchain, and/or the applicable legal rights holder authorized to license the relevant BRAHM-AI material.

### 2.3 “Materials”

“Materials” includes, without limitation:

* source code and compiled code;
* frontend and backend applications;
* API definitions, endpoints, schemas, and SDKs;
* system prompts, instruction prompts, templates, and routing logic;
* model weights, adapters, checkpoints, embeddings, and inference configurations;
* fine-tuning data and evaluation datasets;
* RAG databases, indexes, retrieval logic, and knowledge graphs;
* scripture datasets, translations, explanations, and structured references;
* Panchang, Jyotish, market, agriculture, vision, and language modules;
* algorithms, workflows, helper systems, and business logic;
* voice, STT, TTS, avatar, animation, and lipsync systems;
* user-interface designs, layouts, graphics, icons, and media;
* technical documentation, diagrams, changelogs, and examples;
* product names, logos, slogans, trademarks, and branding;
* non-public operational, security, deployment, and infrastructure information.

### 2.4 “API”

“API” means any current or future BRAHM-AI application programming interface, developer service, SDK, webhook, streaming endpoint, model endpoint, or integration interface.

### 2.5 “Authorized Agreement”

“Authorized Agreement” means a separate written agreement signed or expressly approved by the Licensor, including a commercial license, collaboration agreement, API agreement, partner agreement, research agreement, or contributor agreement.

