## 5. Prohibited Uses

Unless expressly authorized under a separate written agreement, you must not:

### 5.1 Copying and Distribution

* copy, reproduce, republish, mirror, distribute, sublicense, sell, rent, lease, or transfer the Materials;
* publish substantial portions of the Materials in another repository, website, application, dataset, or service;
* package BRAHM-AI code, documentation, prompts, data, or workflows as your own product;
* redistribute modified or unmodified versions of the Materials.

### 5.2 Modification and Derivative Works

* modify, adapt, translate, transform, or create derivative works from the Materials;
* use the Materials to build a substantially similar product, platform, agent, model, API, website, or service;
* recreate BRAHM-AI modules by reproducing their documented architecture, prompts, workflows, or protected implementation details;
* remove, hide, or alter copyright, license, attribution, or proprietary notices.

### 5.3 Commercial Use

* use the Materials for commercial deployment, resale, subscription services, consulting deliverables, managed services, or client projects;
* host a public or private replica of BRAHM-AI;
* offer BRAHM-AI or a substantially similar implementation as software-as-a-service;
* integrate protected Materials into a commercial product without written authorization;
* monetize a fork, copy, adaptation, hosted instance, or derivative service.

### 5.4 AI Training and Model Development

* use the Materials to train, pre-train, fine-tune, align, evaluate, benchmark, or improve an AI model or agent;
* use BRAHM-AI outputs as training data without written authorization;
* generate synthetic training data from BRAHM-AI responses, APIs, voices, avatars, or knowledge modules;
* perform knowledge distillation, model imitation, behavioural cloning, or response cloning;
* extract system prompts, hidden instructions, safety policies, routing logic, or model configurations;
* use the Materials to reproduce the behaviour, personality, language style, knowledge structure, or capabilities of BRAHM-AI;
* include protected BRAHM-AI content in model datasets, vector databases, embeddings, or retrieval indexes.

### 5.5 Scraping and Automated Extraction

* scrape, crawl, harvest, index, bulk-download, archive, or systematically extract BRAHM-AI content;
* use bots, scripts, browser automation, headless browsers, or automated agents to collect Materials;
* extract scripture databases, translations, Panchang data, model responses, prompts, media, or structured API results at scale;
* bypass pagination, rate limits, authentication, quotas, robots instructions, or technical restrictions;
* use multiple accounts, identities, IP addresses, or keys to avoid usage controls.

Normal search-engine indexing authorized by the Licensor is not prohibited.

### 5.6 Reverse Engineering

* reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, decode, or attempt to reconstruct any BRAHM-AI component;
* inspect network activity for the purpose of reproducing private endpoints or internal behaviour;
* derive source code, algorithms, model architecture, prompts, keys, credentials, or protected configuration;
* bypass technical protection measures, feature gates, authentication, subscription controls, or usage metering;
* probe or enumerate undocumented endpoints without authorization.

### 5.7 Security Interference

* conduct penetration testing, vulnerability scanning, load testing, denial-of-service testing, or security research without prior written authorization;
* attempt unauthorized access to user accounts, servers, databases, models, dashboards, logs, or infrastructure;
* exploit or publicly disclose a vulnerability before following the responsible-disclosure process;
* interfere with platform availability, integrity, performance, or security.

Good-faith security research may be permitted only under an officially published security policy or written authorization.

### 5.8 Branding and Identity

* use the names “BRAHM-AI,” “BRAHM True,” “BRAHM Voice,” “Garudaa,” “BRAHM-Panini,” “PotliPay,” “Ramcoin,” or related product names without authorization;
* use BRAHM-AI logos, symbols, avatars, screenshots, designs, or visual identity to imply affiliation;
* register confusingly similar domains, social accounts, applications, companies, tokens, or products;
* falsely represent that a product is powered by, certified by, partnered with, or approved by BRAHM-AI;
* impersonate the Licensor, its developers, team members, products, or official accounts.

### 5.9 Unlawful or Harmful Use

* use BRAHM-AI Materials for fraud, deception, impersonation, surveillance, harassment, exploitation, or unlawful discrimination;
* use the Materials to generate malware, steal credentials, bypass security, or facilitate unauthorized access;
* use the Materials in violation of applicable law, regulation, contractual obligation, or third-party rights;
* use spiritual, medical, financial, identity, or personal-data features in a misleading or harmful manner.

